title: Senior CDC official: Loss of measles elimination status in U.S. would be ‘cost of doing business’
description: The principal deputy director of the CDC said he would not view the loss of the United States' measles elimination status as a significant event.
content: The principal deputy director of the CDC said he would not view the loss of the United States' measles elimination status as a significant event.
